node.statement: CASE 2 - Assume g_1(B) is not equal to B. SETUP: Since a_1 is in B and a_1 is in supp(g_1), we have B intersects supp(g_1) non-trivially. By block property, since g_1(B) is not equal to B, we have g_1(B) disjoint from B. The orbit of B under <g_1> has size r > 1 where r divides |supp(g_1)| = 4+n. APPLICATION OF LEMMA 11.4: |B intersect supp(g_1)| = (4+n)/r >= 1 (since a_1 is in B intersect supp(g_1)). The orbit {B, g_1(B), g_1^2(B), ..., g_1^{r-1}(B)} consists of r disjoint blocks that together partition supp(g_1) = {1, 3, 4, 6, a_1, ..., a_n}.
